Established in 1997, SCIREQ is a world leader in the conception, design and manufacturing of precision laboratory equipment for preclinical respiratory research. We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated individual with a background in software engineering to join our product development team. The ideal candidate has a desire to work in a small business environment with a focus on cutting-edge technology. Working as a SCIREQ software intern, you will use advanced object-oriented techniques to develop data analysis software for our expanding line of scientific apparatus for pulmonary and other research.
 Primary responsibilities:

 Development & improvement of the applications software’s user interface;
 Development & improvement of signal processing & data analysis techniques and algorithms in the application software;
 Experimental validation of said techniques and algorithms;
 Validation of software releases following pre-defined test strategies;
 Maintaining and debugging existing code;
 Documentation of software features and code, including both internal and end-user documentation;
 Limited amounts of second or third level technical support; as it relates to implemented software features;
 Some administrative duties.



 We offer…

 New challenges and a varying array of responsibilities;
 The ability to work on products that enable innovation in respiratory medicine;
 An innovative small business environment;
 A friendly team atmosphere;
 Exciting learning and skillset building opportunities;
 A centrally located office, near public transit.



 Qualifications

 Last year of a bachelor’s degree in software engineering, or similar;
 Applicant must be proficient in SQL and object oriented programming;
 The ability to work efficiently, both independently and in a team;
 Applicant must be curious and willing to take initiative;
 Applicant must be detail oriented;
 English language skills (written and spoken).



 Assets

 Previous software development work experience and personal projects;
 Experience with real-time data analysis;
 Strong math and data analysis skills;
 Familiar with the Agile development process;
 Experience with Embarcadero Delphi and object pascal;
 Knowledge of subversion;
 Knowledge of respiratory mechanics;
 French language skills (written and spoken).



